-- India's L&T calls off merger talks with Future Generali Insurance
-- By Aradhana Aravindan
-- Mon Apr 21, 2014 10:15AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 21 (Reuters) - India's Larsen & Toubro Ltd <LART.NS> said on Monday its unit had called off talks with Future Generali Insurance, a joint venture between local retail chain operator Future Group and Italy's Generali <GASI.I>, to merge their businesses.

The company did not give any reason for ending the merger talks. Last March, L&T General Insurance, a unit of construction and engineering company Larsen & Toubro, and Future Generali had signed an agreement to merge the businesses.